{
  "texts": [
    "To incorporate a new merging method into MergeKit, contributors should familiarize themselves with several key Python modules within the repository:",
    "• merge_methods/base.py: Defines the interface that new merge methods must implement.",
    "• graph.py: Handles scheduling, execution, and data management throughout the merge process.",
    "This is the heart of MergeKit's performance and resource efficiency.",
    "Understanding this module is important to ensure that intermediate results and data movement across devices is handled efficiently."
  ]
}